  <section>
    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>&lt;hgroup&gt;</code> element to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Pair a heading with a subtitle or tagline</li>
      <li>Group a heading with an alternative title</li>
      <li>Associate metadata text with a heading</li>
      <li>Create visually connected heading groups</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The hgroup should contain one heading element (h1-h6) and one or more p or small elements for supporting text. Only the heading contributes to the document outline.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <h3>Default</h3>
    <p>Basic heading group with subtitle.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/hgroup-default.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/hgroup/default" title="Default hgroup" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Default hgroup">{{ defaultCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.eyebrow</h3>
    <p>Small uppercase label above the heading. Place the label <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> first in the markup.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/hgroup-eyebrow.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/hgroup/eyebrow" title="Eyebrow hgroup" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Eyebrow hgroup">{{ eyebrowCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.byline</h3>
