  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Only the heading (h1-h6) contributes to the document outline</li>
      <li>Screen readers announce both the heading and subtitle as a group</li>
      <li>The subtitle (p/small) provides context but is not treated as a separate heading</li>
      <li>Use appropriate heading levels - don't skip levels for visual styling</li>
      <li>Keep subtitles concise to avoid overwhelming screen reader users</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

